rComments: Wow. Professor Orwin somehow manages to combine unbridled passion for Russian Literature, off-the-charts levels of empathy, and great lecture skills into one person. She's the ultimate professor; not taking her course is doing yourself a disservice. The readings are hefty, but they are very good.

Professor Orwin is a good lecturer. She can be a little quiet but can still be understood. She is passionate about the course. There is a lot of required readings and there are quizzes every week or so, meaning attendance is important. I took this as an Econ student who needed a language credit and did not regret it. Class average was a B.

Professor Orwin was amazing. I entered the class last minute due to an issue with another class, so I wasn't expecting very much. But when I attended the class I couldn't help but take in everything she was saying and matching her enthusiasm. She and I have a great discussion about The Greatcoat by Gogol, and the always respected people's opinions
Professor Orwin knows Tolstoy inside and out, and her enthusiasm carries over onto her students.  Also a vert fair grader.  It was always a pleasure taking classes with her.

genuinely nice person. loves tolstoy, and brings great enthusiasm to the class. it's like having your friend's mom teach you: you respect her wisdom and authority, and love her for bringing you cookies. she provides a wonderfull learning experience
Nice lady.  Very knowledgeable in Tolstoy.  Pleasure taking her class.
